race.description: Elders Killara Feedlot Showcase Quirindi Cup Hcp
race.comment: HIBIKI HARMONY (7) has been edging toward a win in her past two city runs, only to be reeled in late on both occasions. She's been freshened 62 days and kept ticking over with a sharp Scone trial. With her natural early speed she can offset the wide draw, take control, and prove very hard to catch. KNIFE'S EDGE (5) keeps leaving himself with too much to do but has been savaging the line. Freshened for this and boasting a strong record at the trip, he's the one who can swoop if they overcook it up front. VORACIOUS (2) couldn't bring up the hat-trick at Walcha when a touch below his best, but he still boxed on for third. He gets an important claim under the big weight and draws to advantage. Can bounce back to winning ways. FIORSUM FRED (6) sets up nicely third-up and should sharpen with the blinkers going on. He backs up quickly from Tamworth and has the engine to be competitive - he'll just need a slice of luck from the wide alley.
